  "_comment": "Object pools for elevation tiles, per terrain and height. Each generated sheet numbers a ROTATING window (elevation.objects_per_sheet items) of its pool \u2014 the pool is shuffled once per (terrain,height) then the window advances for each slot and each re-roll, so different sheets/re-rolls list DIFFERENT objects (not the whole pool reshuffled). Keep pools comfortably larger than objects_per_sheet (aim >= ~18) so rotation stays fresh across the 3 slots and any re-rolls. Pools are meant to grow \u2014 add more ideas freely. Height tiers: base_x_2 low/ground props, base_x_3 medium, base_x_4 tall, base_x_5 towering/monumental. Keep entries terrain-appropriate (they get harmonised toward that terrain's palette).",
